{
  "text": "Single-cell suspensions were made from spleens of IL-5 transgenic mice. Eosinophils were isolated from single-cell suspensions by negative selection as previously described [CITATION_1] . Purity was routinely >98% as assessed by Hema 3 staining. Viability was routinely >98% by trypan blue exclusion.",
  "citation_candidates": [
